{"title": "Hide and Seek", "description": "The artist Valentine Blyth has a very generous heart. He lovingly cares for his invalid wife, rescues a deaf orphan girl from maltreatment in a traveling circus and adopts her, and mentors a young man who gets in trouble with his tyrannical father. The girl, who received the nickname \u201aMadonna\u2019, falls in love with the young man, Zack. Because one of Valentine\u2019s biggest fears is that Madonna\u2019s blood relations will one day trace her and take her away from his home, he keeps the little that he knows of her origins a strict secret. One day, Zack befriends a mysterious stranger, who has just returned from years of rough life in the American wilderness. From that moment, the plot thickens, in mid-19th century dramatic style.<BR><BR>\nThis is Wilkie Collins\u2019 third published novel (1854, read from the 1861 edition). Summary by Anna Simon", "duration": 56160, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "326", "name": "Wilkie Collins"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/hide_and_seek_1511_librivox/hide_seek_1511.jpg", "copyright_year": "1861", "genres": ["Literary Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Anna Simon"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Anna Simon"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Anna Simon"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Annise"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface to the revised edition", "readers": [1724], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hide_and_seek_1511_librivox/hideandseek_00_collins_64kb.mp3", "duration": 245}, {"section": 1, "title": "Opening Chapter. A child's sunday", "readers": [1724], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hide_and_seek_1511_librivox/hideandseek_01_collins_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2270}, {"section": 2, "title": "Book I - Chapter I. A new neighborhood, and a strange character", "readers": [1724], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hide_and_seek_1511_librivox/hideandseek_02_collins_64kb.mp3", "duration